🔁 Step-by-step Git commands

1. Go to your user branch
git checkout user

2. Save your work (IMPORTANT)
git add .
git commit -m "your changes"

3. Get latest main into your branch
git pull origin main

👉 Resolve conflicts if any, then:

git add .
git commit -m "resolved conflicts"

4. Push your updated user branch
git push origin user

5. Merge into main
👉 Option A (best way – Pull Request)

Go to GitHub
Create PR: user → main
Review → Merge